  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study investigates the beneficial effects of prefrontal brain stimulation (with a
      facilitating TMS protocol) before exposure therapy in acrophobic patients. The two exposure
      sessions were realized in virtual reality. Before and after therapy, the phobic symptoms were
      measured on a subjective, behavioral and physiological level. The placebo-controlled single
      blinded study includes 50 phobic patients, which were randomized into verum or sham TMS.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
